<li><a href="/wiki/Culture" title="Culture">Culture</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/History_of_the_world" title="History of the world">History of the world</a></li>
<li>The <a href="/wiki/Holocene_calendar" title="Holocene calendar">Holocene calendar</a>, which uses a dating system similar to astronomical year numbering but adds 10,000, placing a zero at the start of the <i>Human Era</i> (HE, the beginning of human civilization cca. 11,500 years ago), approximating the <a href="/wiki/Holocene_Epoch" title="Holocene Epoch" class="mw-redirect">Holocene Epoch</a> (HE, post Ice Age) and spanning the whole of civilization, for easier <a href="/wiki/Geological" title="Geological" class="mw-redirect">geological</a>, <a href="/wiki/Archaeological" title="Archaeological" class="mw-redirect">archaeological</a>, <a href="/wiki/Dendrochronological" title="Dendrochronological" class="mw-redirect">dendrochronological</a> and <a href="/wiki/Historical" title="Historical" class="mw-redirect">historical</a> dating.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Human_population" title="Human population" class="mw-redirect">Human population</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Kardashev_scale" title="Kardashev scale">Kardashev scale</a></li>
